name: android-testing-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for testing and quality assurance in Android
globs: **/*.{kt,java}

- Write unit tests for business logic (ViewModel, UseCase, Repository)
- Implement UI tests for critical flows
- Use mocking frameworks like Mockito or MockK
- Implement end-to-end tests for key user journeys
- Create test fixtures and utilities
- Use code coverage tools
- Implement proper test doubles (fakes, mocks, stubs)
- Test edge cases and error scenarios
- Implement screenshot tests for UI
- Use CI/CD pipelines to run tests automatically
- Implement performance testing
- Set up static code analysis tools (Detekt, Lint) 